  "root_text": {
    "an3.183-352:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 ",
    "an3.183-352:0.2": "18. Rāgapeyyāla ",
    "an3.183-352:0.3": "~ ",
    "an3.183-352:1.1": "“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. ",
    "an3.183-352:1.2": "Katame tayo? ",
    "an3.183-352:1.3": "Suññato samādhi, animitto samādhi, appaṇihito samādhi—",
    "an3.183-352:1.4": "rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. (…) ",
    "an3.183-352:2.1": "Rāgassa, bhikkhave, pariññāya …pe… ",
    "an3.183-352:2.2": "parikkhayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.3": "pahānāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.4": "khayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.5": "vayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.6": "virāgāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.7": "nirodhāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.8": "cāgāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.9": "paṭinissaggāya ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā. ",
    "an3.183-352:3.1": "Dosassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.2": "mohassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.3": "kodhassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.4": "upanāhassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.5": "makkhassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.6": "paḷāsassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.7": "issāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.8": "macchariyassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.9": "māyāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.10": "sāṭheyyassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.11": "thambhassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.12": "sārambhassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.13": "mānassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.14": "atimānassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.15": "madassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.16": "pamādassa … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.17": "abhiññāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.18": "pariññāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.19": "parikkhayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.20": "pahānāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.21": "khayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.22": "vayāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.23": "virāgāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.24": "nirodhāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.25": "cāgāya … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.26": "paṭinissaggāya ime tayo dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. ",
    "an3.183-352:4.1": "Idamavoca bhagavā. ",
    "an3.183-352:4.2": "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṁ abhinandunti. ",
    "an3.183-352:4.3": "Rāgapeyyālaṁ niṭṭhitaṁ. ",
    "an3.183-352:5.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "an3.183-352:5.1": "Rāgaṁ dosañca mohañca, ",
    "an3.183-352:5.2": "kodhūpanāhapañcamaṁ; ",
    "an3.183-352:5.3": "Makkhapaḷāsaissā ca, ",
    "an3.183-352:5.4": "maccharimāyāsāṭheyyā. ",
    "an3.183-352:6.1": "Thambhasārambhamānañca, ",
    "an3.183-352:6.2": "atimānamadassa ca; ",
    "an3.183-352:6.3": "Pamādā sattarasa vuttā, ",
    "an3.183-352:6.4": "rāgapeyyālanissitā. ",
    "an3.183-352:7.1": "Ete opammayuttena, ",
    "an3.183-352:7.2": "āpādena abhiññāya; ",
    "an3.183-352:7.3": "Pariññāya parikkhayā, ",
    "an3.183-352:7.4": "pahānakkhayabbayena; ",
    "an3.183-352:7.5": "Virāganirodhacāgaṁ, ",
    "an3.183-352:7.6": "paṭinissagge ime dasa. ",
    "an3.183-352:8.1": "Suññato animitto ca, ",
    "an3.183-352:8.2": "appaṇihito ca tayo; ",
    "an3.183-352:8.3": "Samādhimūlakā peyyā—",
    "an3.183-352:8.4": "lesupi vavatthitā cāti. ",
    "an3.183-352:8.5": "Tatiyo paṇṇāsako niṭṭhito. ",
    "an3.183-352:8.6": "Tikanipātapāḷi niṭṭhitā. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an3.183-352:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 3 ",
    "an3.183-352:0.2": "The Chapter on Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed ",
    "an3.183-352:0.3": "Untitled Discourses on Greed, Etc. ",
    "an3.183-352:1.1": "“For insight into greed, three things should be developed. ",
    "an3.183-352:1.2": "What three? ",
    "an3.183-352:1.3": "Emptiness immersion; signless immersion; and undirected immersion. ",
    "an3.183-352:1.4": "For insight into greed, these three things should be developed. ",
    "an3.183-352:2.1": "For the complete understanding of greed … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.2": "complete ending … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.3": "giving up … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.4": "ending … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.5": "vanishing … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.6": "fading away … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.7": "cessation … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.8": "giving away … ",
    "an3.183-352:2.9": "letting go … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.1": "hate … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.2": "delusion … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.3": "anger … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.4": "acrimony … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.5": "disdain … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.6": "contempt … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.7": "jealousy … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.8": "stinginess … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.9": "deceitfulness … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.10": "deviousness … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.11": "obstinacy … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.12": "aggression … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.13": "conceit … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.14": "arrogance … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.15": "vanity … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.16": "negligence … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.17": "insight … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.18": "complete understanding … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.19": "complete ending … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.20": "giving up … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.21": "ending … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.22": "vanishing … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.23": "fading away … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.24": "cessation … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.25": "giving away … ",
    "an3.183-352:3.26": "For the letting go of negligence, these three things should be developed.” ",
    "an3.183-352:4.1": "That is what the Buddha said. ",
    "an3.183-352:4.2": "Satisfied, the mendicants approved what the Buddha said. ",
    "an3.183-352:4.3": "",
